the termios struct contains all data about input and output 

then tcgetattr(0, &t)

here tcgetattr mean  terminal control get attribute
 0 is for stdin

we have 2 types 
raw and canonical

in canonical we need to press enter so input is read by program
in raw the input is directly sent to program

echo is when the terminal prints whatever we type , when input we dont need terminal to print , so we disable echo

read function is used to take input , it is called from unistd

so we make 2 functions 
raw mode and normal model


we  store all flags in variable t with struct termios datatype

raw mode main code:
```
struct termios t;
tcgetattr(0, &t);
t.c_lflag &= ~ICANON;
t.c_lflag &= ~ECHO;
t.c_cc[VMIN] = 0;
t.c_cc[VTIME] = 0;
tcsetattr(0, TCSANOW, &t);
```

normal mode main code:
```
struct termios t;
tcgetattr(0, &t);
t.c_lflag |= ICANON;
t.c_lflag |= ECHO;
tcsetattr(0, TCSANOW, &t);
```


